1
00:00:04,880 --> 00:00:06,140
<i>I never thought...</i>

2
00:00:06,140 --> 00:00:07,640
<i>the relationship between me and P'Mes...</i>

3
00:00:07,640 --> 00:00:09,640
<i>would come to this point.</i>

4
00:00:11,640 --> 00:00:15,210
When I was young, I hated this special ability so much.

5
00:00:15,710 --> 00:00:17,640
It was not fun being a kid you could see ghosts.

6
00:00:18,160 --> 00:00:19,640
Until I met P'Mes.

7
00:00:20,380 --> 00:00:23,320
A strange ghost who doesn't know how he died.

8
00:00:23,680 --> 00:00:25,500
it made realized that...

9
00:00:25,500 --> 00:00:26,960
in this world,

10
00:00:26,960 --> 00:00:28,540
there is still someone more unfortunate than me.

11
00:00:28,970 --> 00:00:30,920
It was sad to think about.

12
00:00:30,920 --> 00:00:32,510
Being stuck in a place...

13
00:00:32,960 --> 00:00:34,350
not knowing for how long.

14
00:00:35,260 --> 00:00:36,730
Then if my gift...

15
00:00:36,730 --> 00:00:38,200
can really help him,

16
00:00:38,640 --> 00:00:39,610
then it could...

17
00:00:39,610 --> 00:00:41,200
really be called a gift.

18
00:00:41,630 --> 00:00:44,840
Somehow it is just like Spiderman saving the world.

19
00:00:45,160 --> 00:00:46,840
But it is not that simple in reality.

20
00:00:47,400 --> 00:00:49,840
And the reason a stupid kid like me is studying law...

21
00:00:50,400 --> 00:00:53,100
is so that might get smart enough to be able to help, P'.

22
00:00:54,720 --> 00:00:56,440
But now I don't know how it happened.

23
00:00:57,120 --> 00:01:00,800
My feelings towards him are strangely changing day by day.

24
00:01:01,420 --> 00:01:03,200
I don't know when it started.

25
00:01:03,820 --> 00:01:05,610
But I know one thing...

26
00:01:05,800 --> 00:01:07,070
I have already felt it.

27
00:01:07,340 --> 00:01:08,890
And it felt really good.

28
00:01:09,560 --> 00:01:10,890
And he is ...

29
00:01:11,640 --> 00:01:13,420
the only one that makes me feel like this.

30
00:01:14,030 --> 00:01:14,990
Right now...

31
00:01:15,600 --> 00:01:17,790
I just want to follow my heart.

32
00:01:52,490 --> 00:01:54,190
I won't let you go anywhere after this.

33
00:01:56,800 --> 00:01:58,220
Go back to sleep.

34
00:06:00,490 --> 00:06:01,310
P'Mes.

35
00:06:08,990 --> 00:06:09,690
You?

36
00:06:16,080 --> 00:06:17,500
How did you get here?

37
00:06:17,610 --> 00:06:19,080
You didn't tell me first.

38
00:06:19,710 --> 00:06:21,880
If I told you before, you would have time to prepare.

39
00:06:23,000 --> 00:06:24,250
Prepare for what?

40
00:06:24,250 --> 00:06:26,250
It's not like I hvae something to hide.

41
00:06:28,620 --> 00:06:29,840
Are you sure?

42
00:06:30,170 --> 00:06:32,080
Are you alright? Look at yourself.

43
00:06:32,940 --> 00:06:34,080
I'm fine.

44
00:06:34,650 --> 00:06:35,900
Just got sick.

45
00:06:35,900 --> 00:06:38,160
Only had to take some medicine and see a doctor. I'll be fine.

46
00:06:38,350 --> 00:06:39,610
No need to worry.

47
00:06:39,880 --> 00:06:41,120
How ca I not worry?

48
00:06:41,120 --> 00:06:42,620
When you have a child you will understand.

49
00:06:44,030 --> 00:06:45,820
I didn't want you to think to much.

50
00:06:46,560 --> 00:06:48,220
Just coming here is tiring enough.

51
00:06:50,330 --> 00:06:51,820
Are you sure that I don't have to worry about you?

52
00:06:53,180 --> 00:06:54,280
Are you sure?

53
00:06:55,610 --> 00:06:56,640
Are you really sure?

54
00:06:56,750 --> 00:06:57,360
What is it?

55
00:06:58,670 --> 00:06:59,390
What is it?

56
00:06:59,850 --> 00:07:01,120
Who reported to you about me?

57
00:07:02,730 --> 00:07:04,120
No one reported.

58
00:07:04,520 --> 00:07:07,320
KhiaoKhiem called me to come stay with you.

59
00:07:07,960 --> 00:07:08,730
KhiaoKhiem?

60
00:07:10,540 --> 00:07:11,610
You believed him?

61
00:07:12,160 --> 00:07:12,640
Oh?

62
00:07:13,640 --> 00:07:15,160
I didn't believe him.

63
00:07:15,160 --> 00:07:17,160
So I came to see for myself and turned out like this.

64
00:07:17,340 --> 00:07:19,500
Who would normally fall asleep 
on a terrace in the rain?

65
00:07:20,060 --> 00:07:21,500
Is there something on your mind?

66
00:07:22,720 --> 00:07:23,580
Do you feel troubled?

67
00:07:24,380 --> 00:07:25,580
Or heartbroken?

68
00:07:26,800 --> 00:07:28,520
Ai'Khiem was just kidding.

69
00:07:31,080 --> 00:07:33,280
Do you want to come back
 home for a couple of days?

70
00:07:34,160 --> 00:07:34,920
I don't.

71
00:07:34,960 --> 00:07:35,420
Oh?

72
00:07:37,290 --> 00:07:39,820
I have an assignment with my friends, 
I already have an appointment with them.

73
00:07:43,100 --> 00:07:44,860
If you are not coming home, then I'll stay here.

74
00:07:45,130 --> 00:07:47,710
I better stay here with you 
if you get sick like this.

75
00:07:48,620 --> 00:07:51,130
Eat some porridge and take
 your morning medicine.

76
00:08:35,500 --> 00:08:36,670
P'Mes...

77
00:08:38,000 --> 00:08:39,850
Where are you now?

78
00:08:50,160 --> 00:08:50,940
<i>Come.</i>

79
00:08:55,310 --> 00:08:57,000
Spring from your feet a bit.

80
00:08:59,000 --> 00:09:00,540
Stay focused. Shoot!

81
00:09:06,680 --> 00:09:07,150
Come.

82
00:09:10,220 --> 00:09:11,680
The wrist. The wrist.

83
00:09:20,110 --> 00:09:21,600
<i>Catch the ball and shoot.</i>

84
00:09:31,440 --> 00:09:32,520
Actually,

85
00:09:32,730 --> 00:09:33,960
if you're not ok....

86
00:09:34,270 --> 00:09:35,790
you don't need to come to practice.

87
00:09:36,000 --> 00:09:37,070
I will tell Peter.

88
00:09:37,550 --> 00:09:38,730
Yeah, right.

89
00:09:39,920 --> 00:09:42,300
You will get sick again if you practice too much.

90
00:09:42,300 --> 00:09:43,360
You're too nosy.

91
00:09:44,410 --> 00:09:46,910
I haven't scolded you for calling my mom yet.

92
00:09:47,680 --> 00:09:48,330
Bastard...

93
00:09:48,720 --> 00:09:50,090
How can you say that?

94
00:09:52,520 --> 00:09:54,030
I am just worried about you.

95
00:09:55,440 --> 00:09:56,440
Ai'Thun...

96
00:09:56,760 --> 00:09:57,880
I'll be honest with you.

97
00:09:59,120 --> 00:10:01,630
Your behavior right now is out of control.

98
00:10:02,060 --> 00:10:03,630
There's nothing wrong with me.

99
00:10:03,880 --> 00:10:05,820
Then why were you shouting on the terrace?

100
00:10:05,820 --> 00:10:07,040
Who were your talking to?

101
00:10:07,040 --> 00:10:07,900
Tell me.

102
00:10:10,200 --> 00:10:11,950
Just calm down.

103
00:10:12,830 --> 00:10:14,160
If you say you're fine, you're fine.

104
00:10:14,570 --> 00:10:16,720
If you don't want to talk to us, we don't mind.

105
00:10:17,580 --> 00:10:19,100
But there's a hotline 165.

106
00:10:19,610 --> 00:10:21,000
They can help you.

107
00:10:21,000 --> 00:10:23,000
You're with him, too?

108
00:10:23,150 --> 00:10:24,300
No...

109
00:10:24,300 --> 00:10:25,180
I just...

110
00:10:25,180 --> 00:10:26,590
If you still want to be my friends...

111
00:10:28,190 --> 00:10:29,950
I am not a drug addict.

112
00:10:35,760 --> 00:10:37,340
Maybe he really isn't a drug addict.

113
00:10:40,840 --> 00:10:42,510
Maybe we are overreacting.

114
00:10:45,470 --> 00:10:46,220
But my neighbor...

115
00:10:46,220 --> 00:10:47,280
That's enough.

116
00:10:58,080 --> 00:10:58,700
P'Mes?

117
00:11:08,240 --> 00:11:08,880
Hey.

118
00:11:09,610 --> 00:11:10,560
Sawasdee, Mom.

119
00:11:10,560 --> 00:11:12,030
Have you changed your taste lately?

120
00:11:12,920 --> 00:11:14,030
Change what taste?

121
00:11:15,130 --> 00:11:16,300
Taste in songs.

122
00:11:16,300 --> 00:11:17,000
Look!

123
00:11:17,000 --> 00:11:19,240
These are all songs back from my time.

124
00:11:20,140 --> 00:11:22,700
But at that time it was not easy to listen to them.

125
00:11:22,880 --> 00:11:24,960
I had to record it from the radio.

126
00:11:25,520 --> 00:11:27,900
Or I had to call the DJ to have them play it.

127
00:11:28,410 --> 00:11:31,040
I made so many tapes at that time.

128
00:11:31,040 --> 00:11:33,040
So I could go back and listen to them.

129
00:11:35,920 --> 00:11:38,410
What happened to make you listen
 to the same music from my time?

130
00:11:38,490 --> 00:11:39,710
<i>This child...</i>

131
00:11:39,710 --> 00:11:42,430
<i>who used to complain about me listening to old songs.</i>

132
00:11:42,600 --> 00:11:44,320
In the end, you listen to them yourself.

133
00:11:44,320 --> 00:11:46,190
Are people listening to the 90's hits lately?

134
00:11:46,190 --> 00:11:47,660
It seems like everything is about the 90's recently.

135
00:11:47,660 --> 00:11:48,860
But here...

136
00:11:48,860 --> 00:11:50,320
I am a true 90's student.

137
00:11:52,040 --> 00:11:54,860
Someone recommended it to me. They're pretty good.

138
00:11:56,330 --> 00:11:58,160
I am a fanclub of GRAMMY.

139
00:11:56,330 --> 00:11:58,160
GRAMMY is a Thai music company

140
00:11:58,160 --> 00:12:00,480
Whoever released a new song, I would know all about it.

141
00:12:00,570 --> 00:12:01,470
This. This one.

142
00:12:03,040 --> 00:12:04,170
This song.

143
00:12:05,280 --> 00:12:06,600
P'Fluke Krekpon.

144
00:12:14,200 --> 00:12:18,280
~ Only ask you to remember ~

145
00:12:20,280 --> 00:12:22,600
~ Whenever you hear ~

146
00:12:23,420 --> 00:12:27,500
~ Please know that this song is for you ~

147
00:12:28,110 --> 00:12:29,800
I though it was Kang's song.

148
00:12:28,110 --> 00:12:29,800
Kang Vorakorn - Porsche from Puppy Honey.

149
00:12:30,090 --> 00:12:31,120
Hey...

150
00:12:31,120 --> 00:12:33,390
This is the original.

151
00:12:33,390 --> 00:12:36,960
At the time, Torfun and Marwin was very famous.

152
00:12:33,390 --> 00:12:36,960
Song is on the OST for Torfun Kub Marwin (1996) Thai Drama

153
00:12:37,080 --> 00:12:39,580
I used to call your dad, WinWin for a while.

154
00:12:39,580 --> 00:12:40,780
Like the main character.

155
00:12:41,020 --> 00:12:42,780
I'm so shy.

156
00:12:46,480 --> 00:12:47,120
Mom?

157
00:12:47,120 --> 00:12:47,720
Hmm?

158
00:12:49,390 --> 00:12:50,490
Do you miss Dad?

159
00:12:52,060 --> 00:12:53,440
I do.

160
00:12:54,860 --> 00:12:56,060
But by now,

161
00:12:56,360 --> 00:12:58,060
your dad...

162
00:12:58,520 --> 00:13:02,120
been reincarnated and is old enough
  to be in primary school already.

163
00:13:04,990 --> 00:13:06,860
Why do you love Dad?

164
00:13:11,720 --> 00:13:14,170
At that time, I had just broke up with my first boyfriend.

165
00:13:14,170 --> 00:13:15,070
So...

166
00:13:15,180 --> 00:13:19,120
Your dad sort of went from the second 
choice to the first choice. Something like that.

167
00:13:19,280 --> 00:13:20,320
It wasn't...

168
00:13:20,730 --> 00:13:24,320
It was nothing. But more like he
 was always a part of my life.

169
00:13:24,320 --> 00:13:26,320
Whereever I went or whatever I did...

170
00:13:26,760 --> 00:13:29,450
he would always take care of me.

171
00:13:29,630 --> 00:13:31,580
Whenever I turned he would be there.

172
00:13:31,740 --> 00:13:33,180
Until one day...

173
00:13:33,720 --> 00:13:35,180
he suddenly disappeared.

174
00:13:35,950 --> 00:13:36,960
I was like...

175
00:13:38,220 --> 00:13:39,390
You are in trouble, Kwan.

176
00:13:39,390 --> 00:13:40,540
You're in trouble, Kwan.

177
00:13:40,830 --> 00:13:42,110
You really love him.

178
00:13:44,170 --> 00:13:45,520
From that moment on...

179
00:13:45,520 --> 00:13:47,520
you dad was always part of my life.

180
00:13:48,220 --> 00:13:49,880
That must be what you call love, right?

181
00:13:52,890 --> 00:13:53,950
<i>What is this?</i>

182
00:13:54,890 --> 00:13:56,170
What kind of feelings are you having?

183
00:13:56,810 --> 00:13:58,170
Why are you asking for?

184
00:13:59,610 --> 00:14:00,480
Nothing.

185
00:14:03,290 --> 00:14:04,480
I'm going to take a shower now.

186
00:14:04,480 --> 00:14:04,890
Ok.

187
00:14:05,920 --> 00:14:07,600
Just go. You stink.

188
00:14:27,850 --> 00:14:29,000
</i>Thun.<i>

189
00:14:29,120 --> 00:14:29,610
Hmm?

190
00:14:30,330 --> 00:14:31,920
It's almost your birthday.

191
00:14:32,200 --> 00:14:33,600
How did you know that?

192
00:14:37,020 --> 00:14:38,440
What do you want?

193
00:14:38,840 --> 00:14:39,980
What do you want to give me?

194
00:14:42,330 --> 00:14:45,610
What can a homeless spirit like
 me what could I give you?

195
00:14:51,200 --> 00:14:53,210
Happy birthday, Thun.

196
00:14:53,210 --> 00:14:56,750
I wish you lots of happiness and hope
 everything you wish for comes true.

197
00:14:56,990 --> 00:14:58,750
If one day I am not here,

198
00:14:58,840 --> 00:15:02,620
when Thun looks up at the stars 
in the sky or in this glass jar,

199
00:15:02,620 --> 00:15:04,620
you will think of me.

200
00:15:05,020 --> 00:15:07,440
Happy Birthday ~ P'Mes

201
00:15:10,480 --> 00:15:12,940
Are you really not here anymore?

202
00:16:18,460 --> 00:16:22,860
Mung Ming Who Doesn't Have A Real Name Like Everyone Else.

203
00:16:33,050 --> 00:16:41,740
[How are you, P'? If you can read this, 
please find a way to let me know.]

204
00:17:18,940 --> 00:17:22,460
Number 2: Two confused hearts...

205
00:17:22,880 --> 00:17:26,490
A destiny beyond your dreams

206
00:17:26,490 --> 00:17:30,270
You will get to live with someone far away.

207
00:17:30,590 --> 00:17:34,540
Heaven cannot stop the path from going.

208
00:17:34,940 --> 00:17:38,700
Your charm can attract both men and women.

209
00:17:38,700 --> 00:17:42,650
Even if you choose to hold, to keep, you can't decide

210
00:17:42,940 --> 00:17:46,760
A sharp sword will cut off the dream

211
00:17:47,050 --> 00:17:50,700
Hesitation, loneliness and fear

212
00:17:51,200 --> 00:17:55,100
Your belief will take you through the storm.

213
00:17:55,100 --> 00:17:58,840
Then the answer you seek will be in your reach.

214
00:17:58,840 --> 00:18:02,650
Right or wrong, it still binds the heart.

215
00:18:02,650 --> 00:18:07,130
Then a light will shine to guide the way.

216
00:18:23,440 --> 00:18:24,750
Hey?

217
00:18:25,240 --> 00:18:26,300
What the fuck is with you?

218
00:18:26,300 --> 00:18:27,770
What the hell is wrong with you, Ai'Thun?

219
00:18:27,770 --> 00:18:29,290
Can't you hear? I said to pass the ball!

220
00:18:29,290 --> 00:18:29,680
Hey!

221
00:18:29,680 --> 00:18:30,680
What is wrong with you two?

222
00:19:08,170 --> 00:19:10,120
If it is like what you said,

223
00:19:10,640 --> 00:19:12,270
are you sure he will talk to me?

224
00:19:15,200 --> 00:19:17,840
Ai'Khiem and I have tried every way.

225
00:19:18,330 --> 00:19:21,320
We almost punched each other.

226
00:19:21,840 --> 00:19:23,320
Is that so?

227
00:19:24,240 --> 00:19:25,960
Then will he punch me too?

228
00:19:27,520 --> 00:19:28,960
Because he is like this...

229
00:19:29,370 --> 00:19:30,380
we want you to try.

230
00:19:30,920 --> 00:19:32,540
If it is not me or Ai'Khiem...

231
00:19:33,640 --> 00:19:35,390
it has to be you, Plaifah.

232
00:19:45,870 --> 00:19:46,490
<i>Thun.</i>

233
00:19:46,970 --> 00:19:47,870
Oh...

234
00:19:48,360 --> 00:19:49,370
Why are you here?

235
00:19:50,030 --> 00:19:51,120
I came to see a professor...

236
00:19:51,320 --> 00:19:52,160
and I missed you.

237
00:19:55,500 --> 00:19:56,960
Ai'Prince and Ai'Khiem put you up to this, right?

238
00:19:59,710 --> 00:20:00,570
Yes.

239
00:20:00,570 --> 00:20:01,840
And since we are at this point...

240
00:20:02,970 --> 00:20:04,060
let me say this.

241
00:20:05,770 --> 00:20:07,230
What's going on with you, Ai'Thun?

242
00:20:08,440 --> 00:20:09,740
We are friends.

243
00:20:10,760 --> 00:20:11,820
You said it yourself.

244
00:20:12,320 --> 00:20:14,490
If there is a problem, say it.

245
00:20:15,770 --> 00:20:16,890
It's nothing.

246
00:20:17,680 --> 00:20:18,170
Thun...

247
00:20:18,170 --> 00:20:18,860
What?

248
00:20:19,390 --> 00:20:20,860
Do you think acting like this

249
00:20:21,360 --> 00:20:22,400
makes you cool?

250
00:20:22,650 --> 00:20:24,400
I told you it's nothing.

251
00:20:24,860 --> 00:20:26,220
You don't want to talk to Ai'Prince...

252
00:20:26,220 --> 00:20:27,260
or talk to Ai'Khiem.

253
00:20:27,840 --> 00:20:29,080
I can understand that.

254
00:20:30,140 --> 00:20:31,210
But this is me, Thun.

255
00:20:32,000 --> 00:20:33,210
What the hell, Plai?

256
00:20:34,890 --> 00:20:37,070
Then you consider me to be like your other friends, right?

257
00:20:40,910 --> 00:20:41,800
Am I right?

258
00:20:42,910 --> 00:20:43,800
Then what about that night...

259
00:20:43,800 --> 00:20:44,560
I'm sorry!

260
00:20:45,920 --> 00:20:47,160
I want to be alone!

261
00:21:12,830 --> 00:21:13,880
So...

262
00:21:14,700 --> 00:21:15,880
Can I sit with you?

263
00:21:24,090 --> 00:21:24,810
Plai.

264
00:21:26,320 --> 00:21:27,290
I'm sorry.

265
00:21:28,570 --> 00:21:29,290
Sorry?

266
00:21:29,920 --> 00:21:31,290
Ai'Thun also said sorry.

267
00:21:31,980 --> 00:21:33,450
Why do you guys keep saying sorry to me?

268
00:21:34,680 --> 00:21:35,450
Well...

269
00:21:36,780 --> 00:21:38,540
I'm sorry for dragging you into this.

270
00:21:42,970 --> 00:21:44,190
We're friends...

271
00:21:45,370 --> 00:21:46,490
then you shouldn't say that.

272
00:21:48,140 --> 00:21:49,870
The way you guys feel worried about Thun...

273
00:21:50,590 --> 00:21:51,870
I feel the same way.

274
00:21:56,750 --> 00:21:57,710
Do you know?

275
00:21:58,460 --> 00:21:59,710
It is so bad...

